  "topic_id": "T02.03",
  "topic_name": "Ratio and Proportion",
  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Ratio and Proportion is a fundamental concept in mathematics that deals with the relationship between quantities. A ratio compares two quantities of the same kind, while proportion states that two ratios are equal. Key properties include: (1) Componendo and Dividendo: If a/b = c/d, then (a+b)/(a-b) = (c+d)/(c-d); (2) Alternendo: If a/b = c/d, then a/c = b/d; (3) Invertendo: If a/b = c/d, then b/a = d/c; (4) Cross Multiplication: If a/b = c/d, then ad = bc; (5) Mean Proportional: If a, b, c are in continued proportion, then b² = ac; (6) Continued Proportion: Three quantities a, b, c are in continued proportion if a/b = b/c.",
    "rules": [
      "Componendo: If a/b = c/d, then (a+b)/b = (c+d)/d",
      "Dividendo: If a/b = c/d, then (a-b)/b = (c-d)/d",
      "Componendo-Dividendo: If a/b = c/d, then (a+b)/(a-b) = (c+d)/(c-d)",
      "Alternendo: If a/b = c/d, then a/c = b/d",
      "Invertendo: If a/b = c/d, then b/a = d/c",
      "Cross Multiplication: If a/b = c/d, then ad = bc",
      "Mean Proportional: If b is the mean proportional between a and c, then b² = ac",
      "Continued Proportion: a, b, c are in continued proportion if a/b = b/c",
      "Fourth Proportional: If a/b = c/x, then x is the fourth proportional",
      "Third Proportional: If a/b = b/x, then x is the third proportional"
    ]
  },
